17
00:00:52,567 --> 00:00:54,188
[SPEAKER_05]: Next is a variance request.

18
00:00:56,633 --> 00:01:00,794
[SPEAKER_00]: Yes, so today we have with us Ms.

19
00:01:00,854 --> 00:01:01,214
[SPEAKER_00]: Chen.

20
00:01:01,974 --> 00:01:02,194
[SPEAKER_00]: Ms.

21
00:01:02,255 --> 00:01:09,396
[SPEAKER_00]: Chen is the owner of Matsuba, located at 38 Riverside Road.

22
00:01:10,197 --> 00:01:22,340
[SPEAKER_00]: So in accordance with 105 CMI 590 of the state sanitary code and the 2013 federal food code, she has put in a request for variance

23
00:01:23,288 --> 00:01:29,234
[SPEAKER_00]: as per the food code section 81-103.11 for acidification of rice.

24
00:01:31,136 --> 00:01:36,461
[SPEAKER_00]: And I'm going to turn this over to Donnetza to explain what the process is and what Ms.

25
00:01:36,521 --> 00:01:37,882
[SPEAKER_00]: Chen has provided us.

26
00:01:38,383 --> 00:01:42,327
[SPEAKER_00]: And this is for sushi, I believe, correct?

27
00:01:43,087 --> 00:01:43,328
[SPEAKER_02]: Yes.

28
00:01:44,955 --> 00:01:48,599
[SPEAKER_02]: So my name is Annette, I'm one of the sanitarians here at the health department.

29
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:55,006
[SPEAKER_02]: So the reason for the variance, so we have adopted the 2013 food code.

30
00:01:55,967 --> 00:02:02,835
[SPEAKER_02]: So whenever the 2013 food code requires a variance request to the regulatory authority,

31
00:02:03,796 --> 00:02:08,959
[SPEAKER_02]: with the evidence that the food does not require time-slash-temperature control for food safety.

32
00:02:09,599 --> 00:02:10,740
[SPEAKER_02]: So Ms.

33
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:30,391
[SPEAKER_02]: Chen is requesting a variance in order to have her sushi rice not being under the, well, acidifying rice for their sushi rice doesn't require to be household, meaning it's not considered non-sushi as food.

34
00:02:30,871 --> 00:02:31,791
[SPEAKER_02]: So that's why we're here.

35
00:02:34,634 --> 00:02:37,196
[SPEAKER_00]: in the documentation that she submitted?

36
00:02:38,116 --> 00:02:48,482
[SPEAKER_02]: She has, yes, so she has provided us with the HACCP plan regarding the procedure on how they're going to monitor their sushi rice.

37
00:02:49,063 --> 00:02:59,789
[SPEAKER_02]: They are using a, which I believe is a calibrated meter, in order to test the pH levels of the set of five rice, sushi rice.

38
00:03:02,287 --> 00:03:14,382
[SPEAKER_02]: And they also have provided us with the Parasite Destruction Consumer Advisory from their proof supplier, where they get their seafood, their fish.

39
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:24,032
[SPEAKER_02]: they gave me the process on their HACCP plan acidification rice menu.

40
00:03:24,473 --> 00:03:34,558
[SPEAKER_02]: So basically as a detailed standard operating, sorry, standard operating procedure where they go in detail how they're going to acidify their rice.

41
00:03:34,598 --> 00:03:35,579
[SPEAKER_02]: What is their procedure?

42
00:03:36,219 --> 00:03:46,145
[SPEAKER_02]: If they cannot lower their pH, which the pH should be below 4.0, then what is their critical point action for that?

43
00:03:49,565 --> 00:03:50,805
[SPEAKER_01]: I hope I summed everything right.

44
00:03:51,406 --> 00:03:57,128
[SPEAKER_05]: Does anyone else do that in the city?

45
00:03:58,708 --> 00:04:03,990
[SPEAKER_02]: Anyone that is doing this procedure, so yeah, I'll go into detail.

46
00:04:04,010 --> 00:04:10,192
[SPEAKER_02]: So anyone doing this sort of procedure that is not in the food code, they do require a variance.

47
00:04:10,673 --> 00:04:17,615
[SPEAKER_02]: So by them satisfying their rights, it doesn't have to be household, which is now considered non-CCS food.

48
00:04:19,581 --> 00:04:21,763
[SPEAKER_00]: So to answer your question too, Dr. Platowicz, yes.

49
00:04:23,024 --> 00:04:36,453
[SPEAKER_00]: Several sushi folks, I don't know, in 2017 Wegmans came in before us to offer the same request for a variance for the acidification of sushi rice.

50
00:04:36,533 --> 00:04:38,995
[SPEAKER_00]: And they had to, like Ms.

51
00:04:39,035 --> 00:04:47,761
[SPEAKER_00]: Chen, they had to submit their standard operating procedures, their hassle plans, their labels and barriers in place to safely administer the process.

52
00:04:49,762 --> 00:04:57,687
[SPEAKER_00]: and all of the procedures that they, like Danetza had referred to, have to be outlined and given to us.

53
00:04:57,707 --> 00:05:00,309
[SPEAKER_00]: So they have satisfied that request.

54
00:05:00,369 --> 00:05:06,413
[SPEAKER_00]: We did grant Wegmans that variance back in 2017 as well.

55
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:11,976
[SPEAKER_04]: And is their plan as outlined similar to Wegmans?

56
00:05:13,197 --> 00:05:15,138
[SPEAKER_04]: It's not different in any material way.

57
00:05:15,158 --> 00:05:17,059
[SPEAKER_04]: So what do you think, Danetza?

58
00:05:17,379 --> 00:05:18,540
[SPEAKER_04]: What's your opinion to us?

59
00:05:19,574 --> 00:05:22,416
[SPEAKER_02]: My opinion is that they should be granted.

60
00:05:22,456 --> 00:05:25,718
[SPEAKER_02]: I see no problem in granting the variance request for Ms.

61
00:05:25,758 --> 00:05:26,039
[SPEAKER_02]: Chang.

62
00:05:26,659 --> 00:05:35,465
[SPEAKER_02]: They have provided the required documents that we're going to need on our end in order to conduct a routine inspection and just make sure that they're doing what they need to do during the routine inspection.

63
00:05:36,966 --> 00:05:45,532
[SPEAKER_02]: And they did provide me, like I said, an action plan if they cannot lower their PHD below 4.0.

64
00:05:51,471 --> 00:05:51,711
[SPEAKER_00]: Ms.

65
00:05:51,751 --> 00:05:58,675
[SPEAKER_00]: Chen, would you like to offer any information or anything different that we laid out?

66
00:05:59,135 --> 00:06:02,717
[SPEAKER_03]: Actually, that's that was everything that whatever.

67
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:05,559
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah, that's what I was planning.

68
00:06:06,279 --> 00:06:10,201
[SPEAKER_03]: So whatever that action that I need to do that we will follow the guidelines.

69
00:06:10,602 --> 00:06:11,142
[SPEAKER_03]: Definitely.

70
00:06:19,119 --> 00:06:20,279
[SPEAKER_00]: Any further discussion?

71
